text: Dzhidzhikhabl () is a rural locality (an aul) and the administrative center of Dzhidzhikhablskoye Rural Settlement of Teuchezhsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 754 as of 2018. There are 8 streets. == Geography == The aul is on the shore of the Gulf of Krasnodar Reservoir. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Circassians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Teuchezhsky District
title: Dzhidzhikhabl
